Class AssertionTools

  • Object
    • AssertionTools

  • class AssertionTools
extends Object
    An internal class that bundles a set of tools that are used in the various assertion classes and can be called directly from test code.
    • fail(String message) - verify.fail(String message)
    • failF(String format, Object[] args) - verify.failF(String format, Object[] args)
    • failWithException(String message, Throwable ex) - verify.failWithException(String message, Throwable ex)
    • failWithExceptionF(String format, Object[] argsEndingWithException) - verify.failWithExceptionF(String format, Object[] argsEndingWithException)
    • warning(String message) - verify.warning(String message)
    • warningF(String format, Object[] args) - verify.warningF(String format, Object[] args)
    • info(String message) - verify.warning(String message)
    • infoF(String format, Object[] args) - verify.infoF(String format, Object[] args)
    Author:
    John Armstrong

    • Method Detail

      • syncInfo

        static void syncInfo()
        Makes sure the testName in OutputInfo.info is that of current test, print testClassName and testName if they have not already been printed, if verboseLevel permits.

        This is the preferred call to make to print these items.

      • fail

        static void fail(String message)
        Like org.junit.Assert.fail, but OutputInfo-aware. Calls OutputInfo.info.printInfoIfNotAlreadyPrinted, then prints its own message, then calls org.junit.Assert.fail with message. Called internally within assertion classes. Can also be called directly through verify.fail(java.lang.String).
        Parameters:
        message - message to be printed
        Throws:
        AssertionError - with message

      • failF

        static void failF(String format,
                  Object... args)
        Like fail(java.lang.String), but with String.format-style message formatting.
        Parameters:
        format - String.format-style format string
        args - zero or more objects to insert into format string
        Throws:
        AssertionError - with message

      • failWithException

        static void failWithException(String message,
                              Throwable ex)
        Like fail(java.lang.String) but prints message and chunked stacktrace of exception to System.out before calling org.junit.Assert.fail.
        Parameters:
        message - message to print
        ex - previously caught throwable object
        Throws:
        AssertionError - with message

      • failWithExceptionF

        static void failWithExceptionF(String format,
                               Object... argsEndingWithException)
        Like failWithException(java.lang.String, java.lang.Throwable) but with String.format-style message formatting.
        Parameters:
        format - String.format-style format string
        argsEndingWithException - one or more objects to insert into format string, including prevously caught throwable object as the last item
        Throws:
        AssertionError - with message

      • warning

        static void warning(String message)
        Calls OutputInfo.info.printInfoIfNotAlreadyPrinted, then prints its own message in form:

        ASSERTION WARNING (<testName>-<fileNameAndLineNumber>): <message>.

        For communicating issue with test without causing it to fail.

        Parameters:
        message - massage to print

      • warningF

        static void warningF(String format,
                     Object... args)
        Like warning(java.lang.String) but with String.format-style message formatting
        Parameters:
        format - String.format-style format string
        args - zero or more objects to insert into format string

      • info

        static void info(String message)
        Calls OutputInfo.info.printInfoIfNotAlreadyPrinted, then prints its own message in form:

        ASSERTION INFO (<testName>-<fileNameAndLineNumber>): <message>.

        For communicating supplementary information about test. May be called at any point in the test, including before code which may cause test to fail.

        Parameters:
        message - massage to print

        Parameters:

        args - zero or more objects to insert into format string

      • getDesc

        static String getDesc(String[] descArg,
                      String dftDesc)
        Helper method for extracting optional description from variadic String array and defaulting to a specified value if array is empty. Compare getDescAsDescArg.
        Parameters:
        descArg - variadic String array of length zero or one
        dftDesc - default description to if descArg is empty.
        Returns:
        description, either from descArg or default
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if descArg array includes more than one item

      • getDescAsDescArg

        static String[] getDescAsDescArg(String[] descArg,
                                 String dftDesc)
        Helper method for extracting optional description from variadic String array and defaulting to a specified value if array is empty.

        Works like getDesc(java.lang.String[], java.lang.String) but packages result as a non-empty desArg which contains either the value from the passed descArg if there is one, else the passed default.

        Parameters:
        descArg - variadic String array of length zero or one
        dftDesc - default description to if descArg is empty.
        Returns:
        description, either from descArg or default
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if descArg array includes more than one item
